It's a word, a very, very specific Greek word that means to be living permanently in a land while citizen of another land.

19:24.917 --> 19:28.583
It means to be living permanently in one country, though a citizen of another country.

19:28.983 --> 19:33.330
So it has a very specific meaning, and Peter knew exactly what he meant when he said it.

19:33.410 --> 19:41.801
And right in that one little word, we've got a wonderful explanation, a wonderful little compendium of what it means to be holy.

19:42.182 --> 19:53.717
Look, if you are living in a country that's foreign to you, you're not from it, you're not native to the country, you're a citizen of another country.

19:54.558 --> 19:58.203
Well, there's really two ways, there's really three ways that you could be there.

20:00.186 --> 20:03.410
The one is to go as an immigrant.

20:03.554 --> 20:19.573
Now an immigrant is somebody who's left one country and you've moved to another country that's not your native country, but you want to become a citizen, you want to assimilate, you want to move in, you really want to lose your old ties and take up your new ties.

20:20.334 --> 20:22.997
The other possible way to come is not as an immigrant, but as a tourist.

20:26.021 --> 20:30.546
A tourist is somebody who really watches the other

20:31.010 --> 20:33.132
this new country kind of through a glass.

20:33.573 --> 20:36.555
You know, there's hardly any real contact.

20:37.156 --> 20:45.785
Tourists tend to go in bands, you know, so they can speak their own language and they can stay in their hotels together and eat in certain restaurants together.

20:45.805 --> 20:47.526
And they really, there's very little contact.

20:47.546 --> 20:48.107
They're tourists.

20:49.088 --> 20:51.510
The other way to go into a country is as an exile.

20:53.472 --> 20:59.378
And I know that that English word has a kind of forlorn sound to it, but that's really the best way to understand

21:00.098 --> 21:03.022
What the Bible means when it talks about how we're supposed to relate to this world.

21:03.062 --> 21:04.684
We're not immigrants and we're not tourists.

21:05.886 --> 21:09.892
We are citizens of the heavenly country living in this country.

21:10.212 --> 21:19.064
We're not immigrants, which means that we know that there's a huge difference between the principles and the customs of this world and the principles and customs of our true country.

21:19.185 --> 21:23.591
And we live in this country with the values of our true country.

21:25.774 --> 21:28.818
Why is there so much pain and suffering in the world?

21:29.026 --> 21:35.016
And how do we handle it in a way that won't destroy us, but could actually make us stronger, wiser, and more hopeful?

21:35.757 --> 21:45.193
All month long on Gospel and Life, Tim Keller is teaching from the book of 1 Peter, and looking at how Peter encouraged early believers who were facing intense suffering in pain.

21:45.914 --> 21:48.498
In his book Walking with God Through Pain and Suffering,

21:48.546 --> 21:56.953
Dr. Keller takes a deeper look at how, with God's help, we can face life's most intense challenges and confront the hard questions on suffering.

21:56.973 --> 22:03.219
Through deep pastoral insight and real life stories, Dr. Keller explores how we can face pain and suffering in our own lives.

22:03.759 --> 22:13.267
This month, walking with God through pain and suffering is our thank you for your gift to help Gospel and Life share the message of Christ's love and compassion with people all over the world.

22:13.768 --> 22:18.532
So request your copy today at gospelandlife.com.

22:18.512 --> 22:23.337
Now, here's Dr. Keller with the remainder of today's teaching.

22:26.461 --> 22:27.322
So we're not immigrants.

22:27.763 --> 22:29.364
We don't apply for citizenship here.

22:30.185 --> 22:30.866
We wouldn't want it.

22:32.388 --> 22:33.629
But on the other hand, we're not tourists.

22:33.829 --> 22:34.170
Oh, no.

22:35.171 --> 22:36.412
Remember what we said this morning?

22:37.233 --> 22:40.117
When God said, some of you do, some of you obviously don't.

22:40.237 --> 22:44.622
When God put the Israelites into Babylon in Jeremiah 29, what did he say?

22:44.662 --> 22:48.466
He says, build houses.

22:48.546 --> 22:58.778
plant gardens, marry and have children, settle down, pray for the peace of that place, identify with the health of that place, and so on.

23:00.160 --> 23:07.629
If you're holy, a holy person's attitude toward this world is neither one of retreat nor of assimilation.

23:08.169 --> 23:15.698
If it's either you're not holy, you're truly living in this world, loving this world, engaged in this world,

23:16.642 --> 23:23.669
ministering in this world at the same time living on the basis of the customs and the laws of your true country.

23:24.229 --> 23:40.365
Now if you want a perfect example of this, at least once a year I like to read this thing, but it just shows the way in which this word strangers orient us to what it means to live a holy lifestyle.

23:41.507 --> 23:45.010
You remember there's a letter that we have from the early

23:45.282 --> 23:46.424
days of the Christian church.

23:46.524 --> 23:47.626
It's not in the Bible.

23:47.846 --> 23:49.929
It's called the Letter to Diagnitus.

23:50.189 --> 23:51.852
We don't even know who the author is.

23:52.292 --> 23:56.519
But it's very, very, very old, certainly the first or second century after Christ.

23:56.879 --> 23:58.322
And it tells us something about Christians.

23:58.402 --> 24:05.352
And in it, the writer says this, Christians busy themselves on earth, but their citizenship is in heaven.

24:06.313 --> 24:07.756
Let me stop for a minute with that line.

24:08.076 --> 24:12.322
Now remember, this is a very, very, very old account of how Christians used to live.

24:12.783 --> 24:14.706
Christians busy themselves on earth, see?

24:14.818 --> 24:18.242
They're not tourists, but their citizenship is in heaven.

24:18.262 --> 24:19.003
They're not immigrants.

24:20.785 --> 24:25.351
And as soon as he pours that out, because that's exactly what Peter says, you're strangers.

24:26.993 --> 24:32.860
Then he goes on and makes several distinctions that show how it affects our lifestyle.

24:33.540 --> 24:37.025
He says, for example, Christians busy themselves on earth, but their citizenship is in heaven.

24:37.545 --> 24:41.490
They marry and have children, but they don't kill unwanted babies.

24:42.562 --> 24:45.085
They're persecuted by all, yet they love everyone.

24:46.207 --> 24:49.431
They share their table with everybody, but they don't share their bed with everybody.

24:50.473 --> 24:52.215
They are poor and yet make many rich.

24:52.796 --> 24:55.740
They're short of everything, and yet have plenty of all things.

24:57.342 --> 24:58.984
Now, there's a wonderful paragraph.

24:59.425 --> 25:01.107
You see what happened?

25:01.127 --> 25:05.333
As soon as the author said, we're not citizens of this world.

25:05.353 --> 25:07.296
We're busy here, but we're not citizens.

25:07.676 --> 25:09.138
He then makes a little list.

25:09.506 --> 25:13.893
of how we're strangers here, because we live on a different set of values.

25:13.933 --> 25:18.099
A holy person is living according to the values of our true country.

25:18.720 --> 25:19.401
What are some of them?

25:19.422 --> 25:24.570
Well, look, first of all, it says, though they share their table with all, they don't share their bed with all.

25:26.553 --> 25:37.650
In our true country, we know that sex is a mechanism, yeah it is, it's a mechanism, for continually renewing

25:37.826 --> 25:43.013
an absolutely total permanent exclusive covenant commitment between two people.

25:44.915 --> 25:46.878
In our true country, we know what sex is for.

25:47.659 --> 25:57.713
Sex is an expression of and a renewal apparatus for a complete total permanent exclusive commitment between a man and a woman.

25:59.435 --> 26:01.778
And therefore, Christians understand

26:01.858 --> 26:06.143
that that's what sex was built for, because that's the way we understand it in our true country.

26:06.163 --> 26:12.469
And so we don't have sex outside of a permanent, binding, total, exclusive covenant, which of course is marriage.

26:13.911 --> 26:14.952
We don't share a bed with all.

26:15.593 --> 26:16.754
We look like strangers here.

26:16.774 --> 26:20.778
We look like aliens here, of course, but that's because we're living according to the laws of our true country.

26:20.838 --> 26:22.320
We understand what sex is there.

26:22.660 --> 26:23.742
These folks around us don't.

26:25.183 --> 26:27.986
Or look, number two, it says they share their table with all.

26:28.006 --> 26:30.169
They're short of everything, and you have to have plenty of all things.

26:30.689 --> 26:31.570
Simple living.

26:32.834 --> 26:36.358
The values of our true country are that God is our wealth.

26:36.639 --> 26:44.488
And because God is our wealth, Christians have a funny attitude toward possessions like we don't care that much about them anymore.

26:47.371 --> 26:48.353
We're short of everything.

26:49.594 --> 26:51.877
If you're a citizen of heaven, you're always short of everything.

26:52.578 --> 26:52.878
Why?

26:53.879 --> 26:55.201
Because you're giving it away.

26:56.442 --> 26:58.785
Because you're so generous, you're radically generous.

26:58.805 --> 27:02.770
See, Christians have a completely different attitude toward money and material possessions.

27:04.258 --> 27:05.620
We share a table with all.

27:07.142 --> 27:09.285
We're short of everything, and yet we have everything we need.

27:10.787 --> 27:15.173
So a different attitude towards sex, because in our true country, there's a different set of values on sex.

27:15.473 --> 27:17.456
In our true country, there's a different set of values on money.

27:17.776 --> 27:21.301
Number three, we're persecuted, and yet we love.

27:23.284 --> 27:26.368
Because in our true country, we really forgive.

27:28.711 --> 27:30.994
In our true country, we know people can change.

27:31.202 --> 27:34.987
You know, in this world that we live right now, people think that forgiveness is for wimps.

27:35.367 --> 27:37.330
And people believe people really can change.

27:37.350 --> 27:38.912
He's always amazes me, for example.

27:39.392 --> 27:41.595
The media will not forgive Chuck Colson.

27:42.076 --> 27:42.897
They won't forgive him.

27:43.598 --> 27:46.441
He was a stinker when he worked for Nixon.

27:46.882 --> 27:49.886
And he admits he was a stinker, and he's repented that he was a stinker.

27:50.166 --> 27:52.990
He did terrible things, and he ruined people's lives, and he lied, and he cheated.

27:53.030 --> 27:55.012
And now he's a converted Christian.

27:55.793 --> 27:56.534
They won't forgive him.

27:56.694 --> 27:59.538
They won't let him, because they consider that wimpy.

27:59.778 --> 28:02.001
You know, you can't let people like that pull the wool over your eyes.

28:02.042 --> 28:02.743
He goes to prison.

28:02.763 --> 28:04.225
He comes out and I'm a born-again Christian.

28:04.245 --> 28:05.247
He expects us to forget.

28:05.627 --> 28:07.310
He expects us to think that he can change.

28:07.570 --> 28:08.652
He expects us to forgive.

28:08.692 --> 28:15.823
In our true country, we do that because we find that ultimately forgiveness is the only way to go.

28:15.963 --> 28:17.846
It's the only way to have a free life.

28:19.088 --> 28:21.732
And lastly, look, it says they don't kill unwanted babies.

28:22.233 --> 28:23.815
And that's something very interesting.

28:23.916 --> 28:28.082
In the Roman world, a brand new born infant

28:28.642 --> 28:35.011
who was a girl, usually girls were, a lot of families didn't want girl babies, or who was just economically inconvenient.

28:35.371 --> 28:42.481
The newborn infant was considered the woman's property and therefore could be thrown out, thrown into the river, left out to be exposed.

28:42.501 --> 28:46.987
What's interesting about Christianity is, women were considered the properties of the men.

28:48.549 --> 28:51.252
The poor and slaves were considered properties of the ruling class.

28:52.915 --> 28:55.538
Brand newborn infants were considered properties of the mother.

28:56.930 --> 29:02.677
And Christianity came against all of that because Christianity is actually a liberalizing influence in this sense.

29:03.498 --> 29:12.709
Christianity has continually, over the centuries, enlarged the circle of respected life, protected persons.

29:13.710 --> 29:16.013
Slaves didn't used to be persons, but now we see they are.

29:16.053 --> 29:17.214
They're not property more.

29:17.254 --> 29:19.937
Women used to be property, but now they're persons, you see.

29:20.618 --> 29:24.082
Newborn infants used to be property, but now Christians say they're persons.

29:25.186 --> 29:30.654
and see we're always cherishing life and enlarging the boundaries of what is life.

29:30.774 --> 29:34.399
Now look, the Christian attitude towards sex, utterly different.

29:34.880 --> 29:36.782
The Christian attitude toward money, utterly different.

29:36.802 --> 29:39.626
The Christian attitude toward relationships and forgiveness, utterly different.

29:40.047 --> 29:42.370
The Christian attitude toward cherishing of life, very different.

29:42.911 --> 29:43.572
Life isn't cheap.

29:45.815 --> 29:48.058
What does it mean to live a holy life?

29:48.819 --> 29:53.906
It means to be a stranger in this world and to have your entire life oriented

29:54.370 --> 30:07.645
around the values of your true country, your true city, you are a citizen of no mean city, you're a citizen of the real city, and you live according to the politics of the kingdom of God.

30:08.146 --> 30:21.561
Now, lastly, we said not only, to be holy means that your mind is completely reoriented and your life is completely reoriented, but lastly, your heart is completely reoriented in this sense.

30:22.181 --> 30:22.802
It says,

30:23.170 --> 30:29.176
Set your hope fully on the grace to be given when Jesus Christ is revealed.

30:29.736 --> 30:34.180
Set your hope fully on the grace to be given when Jesus Christ is revealed.

30:34.200 --> 30:41.747
And what I want to do at this point is transmute you into the final question.

30:42.969 --> 30:44.830
I said, this is what a holy person looks like.

30:45.731 --> 30:48.194
Holy devoted to God, completely committed to Him.

30:48.614 --> 30:49.955
Mind, will, and emotions.

30:50.115 --> 30:52.978
Every part of your life subject to Him.

30:53.282 --> 30:54.284
How can you become holy?

30:54.945 --> 30:55.906
How can you become holy?

30:57.529 --> 30:59.832
The answer is, it all depends on your motives.

31:00.894 --> 31:01.395
Your motives.

31:02.556 --> 31:04.600
A lot of people say, I want to be holy, but I can't.

31:05.441 --> 31:07.124
I want to be holy, but I keep doing this.

31:07.264 --> 31:08.746
I want to be holy, but I keep doing this.

31:08.866 --> 31:10.268
I want to be holy, but I keep doing this.

31:10.308 --> 31:11.090
That's silly.

31:11.370 --> 31:11.951
That's not true.

31:13.093 --> 31:21.586
Jonathan Edwards, in his great book, The Freedom of the Will, a very hard book to read, but one of the great arguments he makes in there is nobody has ever done something they didn't want to do.

31:23.810 --> 31:32.579
One of the big arguments in that book is you have always at every spot in your life, whenever you've had a decision, you have always chosen to do the thing you most wanted.

31:33.780 --> 31:35.502
Well, is that somebody that's not true?

31:36.283 --> 31:36.683
Not at all.

31:37.063 --> 31:44.111
For example, two years ago, somebody took out a gun in a subway and said, give me your purse or I'll shoot you, and I gave him my purse.

31:44.251 --> 31:47.394
Well, now, there's a perfect example of why Jonathan Edwards is wrong, you said.

31:48.034 --> 31:50.497
I'm sure it didn't occur to you at the moment, but it does now.

31:50.857 --> 31:51.538
You say,

31:52.514 --> 31:53.896
I didn't want to give him my purse.

31:54.036 --> 31:55.578
There was lots of money in my purse.

31:55.598 --> 31:57.400
So he forced me to do something I didn't want to do.

31:57.560 --> 31:58.962
Oh, no, says Jack Edwards.

31:58.982 --> 31:59.663
You don't have it right.

32:00.564 --> 32:02.206
You had before you to a choice.

32:02.527 --> 32:04.149
You could live or you could lose your money.

32:04.189 --> 32:06.151
And you did what you most wanted to do.

32:06.191 --> 32:06.892
You wanted to live.

32:10.176 --> 32:12.799
Somebody says, well, you know, I wanted to be holy.

32:13.941 --> 32:15.202
And I didn't want to have to lie.

32:15.503 --> 32:19.087
But I knew that if I told the truth, I was going to be out $20,000.

32:19.468 --> 32:21.330
So I lied.

32:22.050 --> 32:22.971
But I didn't want to.

32:22.991 --> 32:24.574
Oh, yes, you did.

32:24.634 --> 32:26.296
You had before you.

32:27.057 --> 32:36.692
You could either do the right thing, or you could lose $20,000, and you wanted not to lose $20,000 most more than you wanted not to do the wrong thing.

32:37.573 --> 32:51.634
Don't you see, you always do the thing you most want to do, and therefore, the only way to get holy is not to come up with a new regimen, not to come up with new disciplines, not to make New Year's resolutions the only way to become holy

32:53.250 --> 32:55.192
It's only one thing.

32:55.993 --> 32:58.896
It's mentioned a couple times right here in the passage.

32:58.916 --> 33:01.839
You've got to change your motor, your motive.

33:02.099 --> 33:05.363
You know, the word motive and motor are the same word in English, basically.

33:05.984 --> 33:09.467
The motor is the part of the car that gives the car any power and any drive.

33:10.008 --> 33:14.493
Your motive is what drives you at any given point, your deepest motor, what most want.

33:14.833 --> 33:21.320
The only way to change yourself into a holy person is to want to be holy, more than you want to be anything else.

33:21.360 --> 33:23.122
Well, somebody says, how do I do that?

33:24.226 --> 33:25.969
The Bible says it's simple but hard.

33:26.229 --> 33:26.910
You know what I mean?

33:26.990 --> 33:27.871
Simple but hard?

33:29.434 --> 33:29.915
It's simple.

33:29.935 --> 33:31.236
It's not complicated, but it's hard.

33:31.277 --> 33:31.877
It's not easy.

33:31.958 --> 33:33.199
It's simple but very hard.

33:33.360 --> 33:34.021
And here's what it is.

33:34.702 --> 33:38.107
It says, put your hope fully on the grace.

33:38.908 --> 33:53.650
Or if you want another place down here at verse 18, for you know that it was not with perishable things like silver and gold that you were redeemed from the empty way of life handed down to you from your forefathers, but with the precious blood of Christ.

33:54.434 --> 33:58.399
Listen, see that word four in verse 18, that's very important.

33:59.080 --> 34:03.646
Up to now, verses 13, 14, 15, 16, 17, it's been telling you how to live a holy life.

34:04.147 --> 34:13.279
I mean, what it means to be holy, you know, but now suddenly it says, because four, and here it is, here's your motive, four, you are redeemed now.

34:14.981 --> 34:16.763
The word redeemed is a very important word.

34:17.704 --> 34:19.026
It means to be ransomed.

34:19.970 --> 34:25.098
It means somebody has paid a tremendous price to get you out of a predicament.

34:25.739 --> 34:30.606
And so when it says you weren't redeemed with silver and gold, you were deemed by the precious blood of Christ.

34:31.408 --> 34:32.549
This is what it's telling you to do.

34:32.589 --> 34:35.294
If you want to be holy, what do you tell yourself?

34:36.375 --> 34:39.460
Do you say, I want to be holy because I'm embarrassed by these bad habits?

34:40.602 --> 34:45.690
I want to be holy because I want to know that I can lick these things and I can change if I want to.

34:46.591 --> 34:48.594
What do you say to yourself?

34:49.634 --> 34:54.039
Do you say, I want to be holy because there's somebody over there that I really admire and I want to be like her.

34:54.059 --> 34:54.940
I want to be like him.

34:54.980 --> 35:01.368
Do you say, I want to do it because I was always told that I can do anything.

35:01.388 --> 35:02.649
I put my mind to it.

35:03.430 --> 35:04.191
You know, rocky.

35:04.471 --> 35:05.192
I have a tiger.

35:05.312 --> 35:05.893
I can do it.

35:05.993 --> 35:06.574
I can make it.

35:07.455 --> 35:09.937
If you tell yourself these things, I want to be holy.

35:09.957 --> 35:12.120
I want to be sober minded.

35:12.180 --> 35:13.381
I want to be self-controlled.

35:13.762 --> 35:15.163
I want to be like Jesus.

35:15.244 --> 35:17.426
I want to laugh and cry.

35:17.506 --> 35:20.891
quickly and be courageous and be bold and yet be tender.

35:20.911 --> 35:23.215
I want this wonderful character we've been talking about for four weeks.

35:24.316 --> 35:25.118
What do you tell yourself?

35:26.340 --> 35:27.581
There's only one way to get there.

35:28.042 --> 35:31.608
The Bible says you go to the cross or put it this way.

35:31.648 --> 35:35.954
It's not with silver and gold, but with a precious blood of Christ.

35:36.014 --> 35:36.936
What is Peter doing?

35:36.996 --> 35:43.666
He's saying the only way to change your motives is to go to the foot of the cross of Jesus Christ.

35:45.666 --> 36:00.947
and look at the ocean of love that's there and stand on the shores of that ocean and listen to the waves lapping on the shore until the sounds of those waves sink deep into your heart.

36:01.948 --> 36:02.950
What am I talking about?

36:02.970 --> 36:08.978
I hope you know this isn't just theology, it's not just rehearsing something.

36:10.338 --> 36:12.922
What Peter's doing is he's using emotional language.

36:12.942 --> 36:15.066
He's using motivational language.

36:15.086 --> 36:21.636
He says, you have got to think about the preciousness of what Jesus gave for you.

36:21.676 --> 36:30.470
Or put it another way, you will be as holy as you know what your sin costs Jesus.

36:31.973 --> 36:36.700
You will be as holy as you are aware of what your sin costs Jesus.

36:36.720 --> 36:37.842
You stand there

36:38.754 --> 36:44.262
You see the ocean of love, you let it lap on the shores at your feet and you think about it and you reflect on it.

36:45.023 --> 36:45.805
This wasn't silver.

36:45.825 --> 36:46.586
This wasn't gold.

36:46.706 --> 36:47.407
Look at what he did.

36:47.427 --> 36:47.948
Look what he did.

36:47.968 --> 36:48.388
Look what he did.

36:49.871 --> 36:51.553
This is the secret.

36:52.615 --> 36:55.499
You know, sometimes I think every one of my sermons comes down to this.

36:56.140 --> 36:58.283
Sometimes I think every chapter in the Bible comes down to this.

36:58.604 --> 36:59.705
It's simple, but it's hard.

37:00.987 --> 37:04.392
You will never be holy simply by disciplining yourself.

37:04.432 --> 37:05.554
The discipline comes second.

37:06.255 --> 37:08.178
You get holy by changing your motor.

37:09.026 --> 37:13.730
by changing what you most want, and the only way to change what you most want is to go and look what he did for you.

37:14.531 --> 37:16.833
If that means nothing to you, you better cry out.

37:18.475 --> 37:22.439
You better say, Lord God, buy your Holy Spirit, make this real to me.

37:23.460 --> 37:25.462
Let the grace of God begin to teach me.

37:25.502 --> 37:26.703
Let the grace of God come to me.

37:26.803 --> 37:29.766
Help me to put my hope fully on the grace of God.

37:29.966 --> 37:33.489
Now, this works out very, very practically every day.

37:33.529 --> 37:38.674
Listen, when somebody criticizes you,

37:38.754 --> 37:39.775
Do you react in anger?

37:40.636 --> 37:41.877
Or do you react in a holy way?

37:42.097 --> 37:43.999
Well, how do you react in a holy way like Jesus?

37:45.100 --> 37:47.302
Who, when he was reviled, reviled yet not again?

37:47.663 --> 37:48.223
How do you do that?

37:48.243 --> 37:50.465
Do you say, I'm gonna be like Jesus, I'm gonna be like Jesus?

37:50.485 --> 37:50.946
What do you say?

37:51.006 --> 37:52.768
Or do you say, wait a minute, where's my hope?

37:53.488 --> 37:55.010
Is my hope on my reputation?

37:55.070 --> 37:57.392
Where's my hope on the grace of God?

37:58.173 --> 37:59.294
What really saves me?

37:59.354 --> 38:00.395
What these people think of me?

38:00.675 --> 38:01.937
Or what Jesus has done for me?

38:02.617 --> 38:04.139
You stand at the foot of the cross.

38:04.499 --> 38:07.442
You listen to the waves of the ocean of his love.

38:07.554 --> 38:08.936
until it sinks into your heart.

38:09.476 --> 38:10.598
You set your hope on it.

38:14.943 --> 38:25.276
Another way to put it is there's a place where Jesus Christ in John 17 says, Father, for their sake, I sanctify myself.

38:26.077 --> 38:27.699
In other words, sanctify is the word holy.

38:27.740 --> 38:30.603
And what he's saying is, what is he saying?

38:30.723 --> 38:31.805
I sanctify myself.

38:32.205 --> 38:33.307
Jesus was already holy.

38:33.327 --> 38:34.728
What do you mean he sanctifies himself?

38:34.748 --> 38:36.050
But don't you see what he means?

38:36.162 --> 38:42.348
He's to sanctify means to put yourself and make yourself completely committed to something totally.

38:42.869 --> 38:58.625
And what Jesus Christ says is, I have decided to ditch all other concerns and I am committing myself completely in all of my priorities and all of my use of my time and all of my energies and all my creativities to saving and making these people holy.

38:59.606 --> 39:01.688
I'm gonna die if I have to and I have to.

39:01.748 --> 39:03.250
I'm gonna be tortured.

39:03.586 --> 39:11.900
You see, what he's really trying to say is, you know, the son comes to the father and says, they're going to be lost unless we do something.

39:12.101 --> 39:12.622
I will do it.

39:14.325 --> 39:15.907
He sanctifies himself for you.

39:16.749 --> 39:22.138
He sets aside every other commitment and he ditches all competing concerns and he's living for you.

39:22.158 --> 39:23.140
That's what the Bible says.

39:24.302 --> 39:26.706
For their sakes, I sanctify myself.

39:27.170 --> 39:28.272
Now that's another way to put it.

39:28.312 --> 39:29.173
That's just another way to put it.

39:29.414 --> 39:32.739
Take those words for their sakes and set them on your heart.

39:32.820 --> 39:37.087
And I don't care how hard your heart is, I don't care how cold your heart is, it'll melt it.

39:37.227 --> 39:38.950
If you let those words stay there long enough.

39:39.631 --> 39:43.698
For their sakes, Jesus is doing everything for your sake.

39:44.119 --> 39:48.306
He is completely committed to you and to making you holy and happy, which is the same thing.

39:48.578 --> 39:49.860
He's ruling the heaven for you.

39:49.920 --> 39:50.661
He died for you.

39:50.902 --> 39:53.005
The Bible says he has sanctified himself for you.

39:53.446 --> 39:56.891
If you think about that long enough, you'll be able to start to be sanctified for him.

39:57.272 --> 40:01.899
You will only be as holy as you know what your sin cost him.

40:05.345 --> 40:06.246
What does it take to do that?

40:06.286 --> 40:07.989
How many minutes a day do you think about that?

40:08.049 --> 40:14.520
How many minutes a day do you sit and look at that and think about it so you feel it melting you into his likeness?

40:14.800 --> 40:16.082
That's all there is to it.

40:16.610 --> 40:21.115
But listen, as hard as it may seem, I just said it simple, but it's hard, but be of good cheer.

40:21.836 --> 40:23.699
Jesus Christ has sanctified Himself.

40:24.880 --> 40:28.765
He's taking all of His lovely omnipotence, and He's completely committed to making you perfect.

40:29.365 --> 40:30.046
Do you believe in Him?

40:30.066 --> 40:30.807
Have you received Him?

40:31.788 --> 40:38.176
Then you can't miss, you know, because He has made you perfect, and He will make you perfect.

40:38.556 --> 40:44.884
John Bunyan, in his autobiography at one point, he says, now death and death will be where?

40:44.964 --> 40:46.546
Beware what you do.

40:46.914 --> 40:51.620
For I am in the king's highway, the highway of holiness, therefore take heed to yourself."

40:53.303 --> 40:53.743
Amazing.

40:53.964 --> 40:59.031
John Bunyan says, as long as I'm on my way to being holy, he's got a kind of world-defying laughter.

41:00.272 --> 41:01.935
Jesus Christ is committed to my holiness.

41:02.235 --> 41:03.877
He has died so I'll be holy.

41:04.238 --> 41:06.982
He has ripped himself apart so I'll be holy.

41:07.262 --> 41:08.744
I cannot fail to become holy.

41:08.944 --> 41:16.114
The more I look at what he has done to make me holy, and the more I see what he has done to assure that I become holy, the faster I get there.

41:16.386 --> 41:17.768
The faster I actually become holy.

41:18.628 --> 41:19.650
I'm in the king's highway.

41:19.670 --> 41:20.751
Are you in the king's highway?

41:20.891 --> 41:22.413
John Bunyan says, I'm in the king's highway.

41:22.433 --> 41:23.274
I've got nothing to fear.

41:23.374 --> 41:23.854
Are you there?

41:25.996 --> 41:26.557
Are you coming?

41:27.258 --> 41:27.758
Let's pray.

41:29.000 --> 41:40.512
Our father, we ask that you would teach us how to live self-controlled lives, how to live sober lives, how to live lives as strangers here with our hearts fully set and our hope fully set on the grace of Jesus Christ.

41:41.253 --> 41:45.778
As we look at not the silver and the gold that was paid

41:46.114 --> 41:48.338
as our ransom, but as the precious blood of Christ.

41:48.618 --> 41:54.928
And we ask that we might be made holy in the ways that we have been discussing over the past month.

41:55.789 --> 41:57.793
Father, make us holy even as you are holy.

41:59.315 --> 42:00.577
And we ask it in Jesus' name.

42:01.699 --> 42:01.999
Amen.

42:08.069 --> 42:11.154
Thanks for listening to Tim Keller on the Gospel and Life podcast.

42:11.426 --> 42:19.895
If you'd like to see more people encouraged by the Gospel-centered teaching and resources of this ministry, we invite you to consider becoming a Gospel-in-life monthly partner.

42:20.436 --> 42:25.702
Your partnership allows us to reach people all over the world with the life-giving power of Christ's love.

42:26.163 --> 42:29.186
To learn more, just visit gospels-in-life.com-slash-partner.

42:29.626 --> 42:32.670
That website again is gospels-in-life.com-slash-partner.

42:33.791 --> 42:36.434
Today's sermon was recorded in 1993.

42:36.610 --> 42:46.098
The sermons and talks you hear on the Gospel and Life podcast were recorded between 1989 and 2017, while Dr. Keller was senior pastor at Redeemer Presbyterian Church.

